38 /* Peripheral: AAR */
39 /* Description: Accelerated Address Resolver */
40 
41 /* Register: AAR_TASKS_START */
42 /* Description: Start resolving addresses based on IRKs specified in the IRK data structure */
43 
44 /* Bit 0 : */
45 #define AAR_TASKS_START_TASKS_START_Pos (0UL)
46 #define AAR_TASKS_START_TASKS_START_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_TASKS_START_TASKS_START_Pos)
48 /* Register: AAR_TASKS_STOP */
49 /* Description: Stop resolving addresses */
50 
51 /* Bit 0 : */
52 #define AAR_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Pos (0UL)
53 #define AAR_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Pos)
55 /* Register: AAR_EVENTS_END */
56 /* Description: Address resolution procedure complete */
57 
58 /* Bit 0 : */
59 #define AAR_EVENTS_END_EVENTS_END_Pos (0UL)
60 #define AAR_EVENTS_END_EVENTS_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_EVENTS_END_EVENTS_END_Pos)
62 /* Register: AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED */
63 /* Description: Address resolved */
64 
65 /* Bit 0 : */
66 #define AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED_EVENTS_RESOLVED_Pos (0UL)
67 #define AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED_EVENTS_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED_EVENTS_RESOLVED_Pos)
69 /* Register: AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED */
70 /* Description: Address not resolved */
71 
72 /* Bit 0 : */
73 #define AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (0UL)
74 #define AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
76 /* Register: AAR_INTENSET */
77 /* Description: Enable interrupt */
78 
79 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to enable interrupt for NOTRESOLVED event */
80 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
81 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
82 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
83 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
84 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Set (1UL)
86 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to enable interrupt for RESOLVED event */
87 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
88 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos)
89 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
90 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
91 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Set (1UL)
93 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to enable interrupt for END event */
94 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos (0UL)
95 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos)
96 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Disabled (0UL)
97 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Enabled (1UL)
98 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Set (1UL)
100 /* Register: AAR_INTENCLR */
101 /* Description: Disable interrupt */
102 
103 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to disable interrupt for NOTRESOLVED event */
104 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
105 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
106 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
107 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
108 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
110 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to disable interrupt for RESOLVED event */
111 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
112 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos)
113 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
114 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
115 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
117 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to disable interrupt for END event */
118 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos (0UL)
119 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos)
120 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Disabled (0UL)
121 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Enabled (1UL)
122 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Clear (1UL)
124 /* Register: AAR_STATUS */
125 /* Description: Resolution status */
126 
127 /* Bits 3..0 : The IRK that was used last time an address was resolved */
128 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos (0UL)
129 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Msk (0xFUL << AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos)
131 /* Register: AAR_ENABLE */
132 /* Description: Enable AAR */
133 
134 /* Bits 1..0 : Enable or disable AAR */
135 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos (0UL)
136 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Msk (0x3UL << AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos)
137 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Disabled (0UL)
138 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Enabled (3UL)
140 /* Register: AAR_NIRK */
141 /* Description: Number of IRKs */
142 
143 /* Bits 4..0 : Number of Identity root keys available in the IRK data structure */
144 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos (0UL)
145 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Msk (0x1FUL << AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos)
147 /* Register: AAR_IRKPTR */
148 /* Description: Pointer to IRK data structure */
149 
150 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to the IRK data structure */
151 #define AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Pos (0UL)
152 #define AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Pos)
154 /* Register: AAR_ADDRPTR */
155 /* Description: Pointer to the resolvable address */
156 
157 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to the resolvable address (6-bytes) */
158 #define AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Pos (0UL)
159 #define AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Pos)
161 /* Register: AAR_SCRATCHPTR */
162 /* Description: Pointer to data area used for temporary storage */
163 
164 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to a scratch data area used for temporary storage during resolution.A space of minimum 3 bytes must be reserved. */
165 #define AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos (0UL)
166 #define AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos)
169 /* Peripheral: ACL */
170 /* Description: Access control lists */
171 
172 /* Register: ACL_ACL_ADDR */
173 /* Description: Description cluster[n]: Configure the word-aligned start address of region n to protect */
174 
175 /* Bits 31..0 : Valid word-aligned start address of region n to protect. Address must point to a flash page boundary. */
176 #define ACL_ACL_ADDR_ADDR_Pos (0UL)
177 #define ACL_ACL_ADDR_ADDR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << ACL_ACL_ADDR_ADDR_Pos)
179 /* Register: ACL_ACL_SIZE */
180 /* Description: Description cluster[n]: Size of region to protect counting from address ACL[n].ADDR. Write '0' as no effect. */
181 
182 /* Bits 31..0 : Size of flash region n in bytes. Must be a multiple of the flash page size, and the maximum region size is limited to 512kB. */
183 #define ACL_ACL_SIZE_SIZE_Pos (0UL)
184 #define ACL_ACL_SIZE_SIZE_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << ACL_ACL_SIZE_SIZE_Pos)
186 /* Register: ACL_ACL_PERM */
187 /* Description: Description cluster[n]: Access permissions for region n as defined by start address ACL[n].ADDR and size ACL[n].SIZE */
188 
189 /* Bit 2 : Configure read permissions for region n. Write '0' has no effect. */
190 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_READ_Pos (2UL)
191 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_READ_Msk (0x1UL << ACL_ACL_PERM_READ_Pos)
192 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_READ_Enable (0UL)
193 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_READ_Disable (1UL)
195 /* Bit 1 : Configure write and erase permissions for region n. Write '0' has no effect. */
196 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_WRITE_Pos (1UL)
197 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_WRITE_Msk (0x1UL << ACL_ACL_PERM_WRITE_Pos)
198 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_WRITE_Enable (0UL)
199 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_WRITE_Disable (1UL)
202 /* Peripheral: CCM */
203 /* Description: AES CCM Mode Encryption */
204 
205 /* Register: CCM_TASKS_KSGEN */
206 /* Description: Start generation of key-stream. This operation will stop by itself when completed. */
207 
208 /* Bit 0 : */
209 #define CCM_TASKS_KSGEN_TASKS_KSGEN_Pos (0UL)
210 #define CCM_TASKS_KSGEN_TASKS_KSGEN_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_TASKS_KSGEN_TASKS_KSGEN_Pos)
212 /* Register: CCM_TASKS_CRYPT */
213 /* Description: Start encryption/decryption. This operation will stop by itself when completed. */
214 
215 /* Bit 0 : */
216 #define CCM_TASKS_CRYPT_TASKS_CRYPT_Pos (0UL)
217 #define CCM_TASKS_CRYPT_TASKS_CRYPT_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_TASKS_CRYPT_TASKS_CRYPT_Pos)
219 /* Register: CCM_TASKS_STOP */
220 /* Description: Stop encryption/decryption */
221 
222 /* Bit 0 : */
223 #define CCM_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Pos (0UL)
224 #define CCM_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Pos)
226 /* Register: CCM_TASKS_RATEOVERRIDE */
227 /* Description: Override DATARATE setting in MODE register with the contents of the RATEOVERRIDE register for any ongoing encryption/decryption */
228 
229 /* Bit 0 : */
230 #define CCM_TASKS_RATEOVERRIDE_TASKS_RATEOVERRIDE_Pos (0UL)
231 #define CCM_TASKS_RATEOVERRIDE_TASKS_RATEOVERRIDE_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_TASKS_RATEOVERRIDE_TASKS_RATEOVERRIDE_Pos)
233 /* Register: CCM_EVENTS_ENDKSGEN */
234 /* Description: Key-stream generation complete */
235 
236 /* Bit 0 : */
237 #define CCM_EVENTS_ENDKSGEN_EVENTS_ENDKSGEN_Pos (0UL)
238 #define CCM_EVENTS_ENDKSGEN_EVENTS_ENDKSGEN_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_EVENTS_ENDKSGEN_EVENTS_ENDKSGEN_Pos)
240 /* Register: CCM_EVENTS_ENDCRYPT */
241 /* Description: Encrypt/decrypt complete */
242 
243 /* Bit 0 : */
244 #define CCM_EVENTS_ENDCRYPT_EVENTS_ENDCRYPT_Pos (0UL)
245 #define CCM_EVENTS_ENDCRYPT_EVENTS_ENDCRYPT_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_EVENTS_ENDCRYPT_EVENTS_ENDCRYPT_Pos)
247 /* Register: CCM_EVENTS_ERROR */
248 /* Description: Deprecated register - CCM error event */
249 
250 /* Bit 0 : */
251 #define CCM_EVENTS_ERROR_EVENTS_ERROR_Pos (0UL)
252 #define CCM_EVENTS_ERROR_EVENTS_ERROR_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_EVENTS_ERROR_EVENTS_ERROR_Pos)
254 /* Register: CCM_SHORTS */
255 /* Description: Shortcut register */
256 
257 /* Bit 0 : Shortcut between ENDKSGEN event and CRYPT task */
258 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Pos (0UL)
259 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Pos)
260 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Disabled (0UL)
261 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Enabled (1UL)
263 /* Register: CCM_INTENSET */
264 /* Description: Enable interrupt */
265 
266 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to enable interrupt for ERROR event */
267 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Pos (2UL)
268 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Pos)
269 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Disabled (0UL)
270 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Enabled (1UL)
271 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Set (1UL)
273 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to enable interrupt for ENDCRYPT event */
274 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Pos (1UL)
275 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Pos)
276 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Disabled (0UL)
277 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Enabled (1UL)
278 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Set (1UL)
280 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to enable interrupt for ENDKSGEN event */
281 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Pos (0UL)
282 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Pos)
283 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Disabled (0UL)
284 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Enabled (1UL)
285 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Set (1UL)
287 /* Register: CCM_INTENCLR */
288 /* Description: Disable interrupt */
289 
290 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to disable interrupt for ERROR event */
291 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Pos (2UL)
292 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Pos)
293 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Disabled (0UL)
294 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Enabled (1UL)
295 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Clear (1UL)
297 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to disable interrupt for ENDCRYPT event */
298 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Pos (1UL)
299 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Pos)
300 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Disabled (0UL)
301 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Enabled (1UL)
302 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Clear (1UL)
304 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to disable interrupt for ENDKSGEN event */
305 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Pos (0UL)
306 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Pos)
307 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Disabled (0UL)
308 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Enabled (1UL)
309 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Clear (1UL)
311 /* Register: CCM_MICSTATUS */
312 /* Description: MIC check result */
313 
314 /* Bit 0 : The result of the MIC check performed during the previous decryption operation */
315 #define CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_Pos (0UL)
316 #define CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_Pos)
317 #define CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_CheckFailed (0UL)
318 #define CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_CheckPassed (1UL)
320 /* Register: CCM_ENABLE */
321 /* Description: Enable */
322 
323 /* Bits 1..0 : Enable or disable CCM */
324 #define CCM_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos (0UL)
325 #define CCM_ENABLE_ENABLE_Msk (0x3UL << CCM_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos)
326 #define CCM_ENABLE_ENABLE_Disabled (0UL)
327 #define CCM_ENABLE_ENABLE_Enabled (2UL)
329 /* Register: CCM_MODE */
330 /* Description: Operation mode */
331 
332 /* Bit 24 : Packet length configuration */
333 #define CCM_MODE_LENGTH_Pos (24UL)
334 #define CCM_MODE_LENGTH_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_MODE_LENGTH_Pos)
335 #define CCM_MODE_LENGTH_Default (0UL)
336 #define CCM_MODE_LENGTH_Extended (1UL)
338 /* Bits 17..16 : Radio data rate that the CCM shall run synchronous with */
339 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_Pos (16UL)
340 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_Msk (0x3UL << CCM_MODE_DATARATE_Pos)
341 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_1Mbit (0UL)
342 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_2Mbit (1UL)
343 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_125Kbps (2UL)
344 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_500Kbps (3UL)
346 /* Bit 0 : The mode of operation to be used. The settings in this register apply whenever either the KSGEN or CRYPT tasks are triggered. */
347 #define CCM_MODE_MODE_Pos (0UL)
348 #define CCM_MODE_MODE_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_MODE_MODE_Pos)
349 #define CCM_MODE_MODE_Encryption (0UL)
350 #define CCM_MODE_MODE_Decryption (1UL)
352 /* Register: CCM_CNFPTR */
353 /* Description: Pointer to data structure holding AES key and NONCE vector */
354 
355 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to the data structure holding the AES key and the CCM NONCE vector (see Table 1 CCM data structure overview) */
356 #define CCM_CNFPTR_CNFPTR_Pos (0UL)
357 #define CCM_CNFPTR_CNFPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << CCM_CNFPTR_CNFPTR_Pos)
359 /* Register: CCM_INPTR */
360 /* Description: Input pointer */
361 
362 /* Bits 31..0 : Input pointer */
363 #define CCM_INPTR_INPTR_Pos (0UL)
364 #define CCM_INPTR_INPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << CCM_INPTR_INPTR_Pos)
366 /* Register: CCM_OUTPTR */
367 /* Description: Output pointer */
368 
369 /* Bits 31..0 : Output pointer */
370 #define CCM_OUTPTR_OUTPTR_Pos (0UL)
371 #define CCM_OUTPTR_OUTPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << CCM_OUTPTR_OUTPTR_Pos)
373 /* Register: CCM_SCRATCHPTR */
374 /* Description: Pointer to data area used for temporary storage */
375 
376 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to a scratch data area used for temporary storage during key-stream generation,
377  MIC generation and encryption/decryption. */
378 #define CCM_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos (0UL)
379 #define CCM_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << CCM_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos)
381 /* Register: CCM_MAXPACKETSIZE */
382 /* Description: Length of key-stream generated when MODE.LENGTH = Extended. */
383 
384 /* Bits 7..0 : Length of key-stream generated when MODE.LENGTH = Extended. This value must be greater or equal to the subsequent packet payload to be encrypted/decrypted. */
385 #define CCM_MAXPACKETSIZE_MAXPACKETSIZE_Pos (0UL)
386 #define CCM_MAXPACKETSIZE_MAXPACKETSIZE_Msk (0xFFUL << CCM_MAXPACKETSIZE_MAXPACKETSIZE_Pos)
388 /* Register: CCM_RATEOVERRIDE */
389 /* Description: Data rate override setting. */
390 
391 /* Bits 1..0 : Data rate override setting. */
392 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_Pos (0UL)
393 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_Msk (0x3UL << CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_Pos)
394 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_1Mbit (0UL)
395 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_2Mbit (1UL)
396 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_125Kbps (2UL)
397 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_500Kbps (3UL)
400 /* Peripheral: CC_HOST_RGF */
401 /* Description: CRYPTOCELL HOST_RGF interface */
402 
403 /* Register: CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL */
404 /* Description: AES hardware key select */
405 
406 /* Bits 1..0 : Select the source of the HW key that is used by the AES engine */
407 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_Pos (0UL)
408 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_Msk (0x3UL << CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_Pos)
409 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_K_DR (0UL)
410 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_K_PRTL (1UL)
411 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_HOST_CRYPTOKEY_SEL_Session (2UL)
413 /* Register: CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KPRTL_LOCK */
414 /* Description: This write-once register is the K_PRTL lock register. When this register is set, K_PRTL can not be used and a zeroed key will be used instead. The value of this register is saved in the CRYPTOCELL AO power domain. */
415 
416 /* Bit 0 : This register is the K_PRTL lock register. When this register is set, K_PRTL can not be used and a zeroed key will be used instead. The value of this register is saved in the CRYPTOCELL AO power domain. */
417 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KPRTL_LOCK_HOST_IOT_KPRTL_LOCK_Pos (0UL)
418 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KPRTL_LOCK_HOST_IOT_KPRTL_LOCK_Msk (0x1UL << CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KPRTL_LOCK_HOST_IOT_KPRTL_LOCK_Pos)
419 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KPRTL_LOCK_HOST_IOT_KPRTL_LOCK_Disabled (0UL)
420 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KPRTL_LOCK_HOST_IOT_KPRTL_LOCK_Enabled (1UL)
422 /* Register: CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KDR0 */
423 /* Description: This register holds bits 31:0 of K_DR. The value of this register is saved in the CRYPTOCELL AO power domain. Reading from this address returns the K_DR valid status indicating if K_DR is successfully retained. */
424 
425 /* Bits 31..0 : Write: K_DR bits 31:0 Read: 0x00000000 when 128-bit K_DR key value is not yet retained in the CRYPTOCELL AO power domain Read: 0x00000001 when 128-bit K_DR key value is successfully retained in the CRYPTOCELL AO power domain */
426 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KDR0_HOST_IOT_KDR0_Pos (0UL)
427 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KDR0_HOST_IOT_KDR0_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KDR0_HOST_IOT_KDR0_Pos)
429 /* Register: CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KDR1 */
430 /* Description: This register holds bits 63:32 of K_DR. The value of this register is saved in the CRYPTOCELL AO power domain. */
431 
432 /* Bits 31..0 : K_DR bits 63:32 */
433 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KDR1_HOST_IOT_KDR1_Pos (0UL)
434 #define CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KDR1_HOST_IOT_KDR1_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KDR1_HOST_IOT_KDR1_Pos)
436 /* Register: CC_HOST_RGF_HOST_IOT_KDR2 */
437 /* Description: This register holds bits 95:64 of K_DR. The value of this register is saved in the CRYPTOCELL AO power domain. */
438 
439 /* Bits 31..0 : K_DR bits 95:64 */

6413 /* Register: GPIO_LATCH */
6414 /* Description: Latch register indicating what GPIO pins that have met the criteria set in the PIN_CNF[n].SENSE registers */
6415 
6416 /* Bit 31 : Status on whether PIN31 has met criteria set in PIN_CNF31.SENSE register. Write '1' to clear. */

6419 #define GPIO_LATCH_PIN31_NotLatched (0UL)
6420 #define GPIO_LATCH_PIN31_Latched (1UL)
